BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 181.2 720 Td (Chapter 2: Benjamin's Kite) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (By candlelight, Zara opened a book about the history of electricity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('In 1752, Benjamin Franklin flew a kite in a thunderstorm!' she read.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (He attached a metal key to the kite string and waited for lightning.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (When lightning hit nearby, electricity traveled down the wet string to the key!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (A spark jumped from the key - proving that lightning IS electricity!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('That was incredibly dangerous,' Zara noted, 'but it changed science forever!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: STATIC vs CURRENT ELECTRICITY) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Static electricity: charges build up on a surface \(like rubbing a balloon on hair\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Current electricity: charges flow continuously through a conductor \(like in wires\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Lightning is static electricity on a massive scale - billions of volts!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Static builds up from friction - electrons transfer from one material to another.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Current electricity is what powers our homes - a steady flow of electrons in wires.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* A lightning bolt carries about 300 million volts and 30,000 amps!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Static electricity is why you get shocked touching a doorknob in winter.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Ben Franklin also invented the lightning rod to protect buildings.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Rub a balloon on your hair, then hold it near small paper bits. Watch them jump! That is static!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Why do you get more static shocks in winter than in summer?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
