BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 176.4 720 Td (Chapter 3: The Circuit Path) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (The next day \(power still out\), Zara found a flashlight with batteries.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (She took it apart carefully. 'Battery, wires, switch, bulb,' she listed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('It is a circuit! Electricity flows in a complete loop from the battery.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (She noticed when she broke the loop \(turned off the switch\), the light went out.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('The electricity needs a complete path to flow! No gaps allowed!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (She experimented - a paper clip completed the circuit; paper did not. Fascinating!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: CIRCUITS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (A circuit is a complete path for electricity to flow through.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Every circuit needs: a power source, a conductor \(wire\), and a load \(like a bulb\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Conductors let electricity flow easily: metals like copper, gold, aluminum.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Insulators block electricity: rubber, plastic, glass, wood.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (A switch opens or closes the circuit - when open, electricity cannot flow.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (If there is ANY break in the circuit, electricity stops flowing completely!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* Copper is used in most wiring because it conducts electricity very well and is affordable.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Your body is a conductor! That is why you can get an electric shock \(be careful!\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* Series circuits have one path; parallel circuits have multiple paths for electricity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Connect a battery to a small LED bulb with two wires. You built a circuit! Add a switch \(paper clip\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (Why are electrical wires covered in plastic or rubber?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
